    "Differential_Diagnosis": {
      "text": "",
      "subsections": {
        "Myalgia": {
          "text": "Infection:\nViral infection\n(e.g.\nInfluenza\n)\nBacterial infection\nSpirochete infection (E.g.\nDengue fever\n;\nTrichinella\n)\nDrugs:\nStatins\nBisphosphonates\nCorticosteroids\nCiprofloxacin\nClofibrate\nColchicine\nChloroquine\nEmetine\nAminocaproic acid\nZidovudine\nBretylium\nPenicillamine\nDrugs causing\nhypokalemia\nMetabolic disorders:\nVitamin D deficiency\nMitochondrial myopathy\nScurvy\nOsteomalacia\nFibromyalgia\nEndocrine:\nHypothyroidism\nHyperthyroidism\nCushing’s syndrome\nAdrenal insufficiency\nHyperparathyroidism\nPolymyalgia rheumatica\nRhabdomyolysis\nMyositis\nPolymyositis\nDermatomyositis\nMyositis (peds)\nSystemic lupus erythematosus\nRheumatoid arthritis\nInclusion body myositis\nSarcoidosis\nScleroderma\nSjögren’s syndrome\nPsychiatric (e.g. somatic manifestations of\ndepression\n)\nDomestic abuse\nCrush injury\nLyme disease\nEhlers-Danlos syndrome\n(hypermobility syndrome)\nHIV\nmyopathy\nHypophosphatemia\nHypokalemia\nHypothermia\nProlonged immobility\nStrenuous exercise (overuse) or\nheat stroke\nSeizure\nSevere\nvolume contraction\nAlcoholism\nMuscular dystrophy\nDuchenne\nBecker\nLimb-girdle\nFacioscapulohumeral\nMyotonic dystrophy\nMyotonia congenita\nCompartment syndrome\n; Muscle infarction\nNeuropathic\nChronic fatigue syndrome\nVasculitis\nSarcocystosis\nSpinal stenosis\nDiabetic lumbosacral plexopathy",
